{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern.unify?\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">Pattern</span>.<span class=\"name\">unify?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern\">Pattern</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">zetaDelta</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool.true\">true</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult\">MatchUnifyResult</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Attempts to unify expression `e` against pattern `p`, allowing metavariables in `e`.\n\nReturns `some result` if unification succeeds, where `result` contains:\n- `us`: Level assignments for the pattern's universe variables\n- `args`: Expression assignments for the pattern's bound variables\n\nUnlike `match?`, this handles terms containing metavariables by deferring\nconstraints to Phase 2 unification. Use this when matching against goal\nexpressions that may contain unsolved metavariables.\n\nInstance arguments are synthesized (or assigned by unification). Any that cannot be resolved are\nreported in `MatchUnifyResult.unresolvedInsts` rather than silently left as loose metavariables in\n`args`. Proof arguments are skipped via proof irrelevance.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern.unify?","kind":"def","line":1178,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern.unify?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L1178-L1194"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern.match?\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">Pattern</span>.<span class=\"name\">match?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern\">Pattern</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">zetaDelta</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool.true\">true</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult\">MatchUnifyResult</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Attempts to match expression `e` against pattern `p` using purely syntactic matching.\n\nReturns `some result` if matching succeeds, where `result` contains:\n- `us`: Level assignments for the pattern's universe variables\n- `args`: Expression assignments for the pattern's bound variables\n\nMatching fails if:\n- The term contains metavariables (use `unify?` instead)\n- Structural mismatch after reducible unfolding\n\nInstance arguments are synthesized (or assigned by unification). Any that cannot be resolved are\nreported in `MatchUnifyResult.unresolvedInsts` rather than silently left as loose metavariables in\n`args`. Proof arguments are skipped via proof irrelevance.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern.match?","kind":"def","line":1160,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern.match?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L1160-L1176"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.unresolvedInsts\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">MatchUnifyResult</span>.<span class=\"name\">unresolvedInsts</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult\">MatchUnifyResult</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.MVarId\">MVarId</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Instance arguments that could not be synthesized, nor assigned while processing pending\nconstraints. `args` still holds a fresh, unassigned metavariable for each of them. A consumer that\nsplices `args` into a proof term (e.g. `BackwardRule.apply`) must treat a non-empty array as\nfailure; a purely structural matcher may ignore it.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.unresolvedInsts","kind":"def","line":1142,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.unresolvedInsts","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L1142-L1142"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.args\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">MatchUnifyResult</span>.<span class=\"name\">args</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult\">MatchUnifyResult</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.args","kind":"def","line":1135,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.args","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L1135-L1135"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.us\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">MatchUnifyResult</span>.<span class=\"name\">us</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult\">MatchUnifyResult</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Level.html#Lean.Level\">Level</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.us","kind":"def","line":1134,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.us","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L1134-L1134"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">MatchUnifyResult</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Level.html#Lean.Level\">Lean.Level</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.MVarId\">Lean.MVarId</a></span> → <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult\">Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult</a></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.mk","kind":"ctor","line":1133,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L1133-L1142"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">MatchUnifyResult</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult","kind":"structure","line":1133,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.MatchUnifyResult","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L1133-L1142"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.isDefEqS\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">isDefEqS</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">t </span><span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">unify </span><span class=\"fn\">zetaDelta</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool.true\">true</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">mvarsNew </span><span class=\"fn\">mvarsToCheckType</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.MVarId\">MVarId</a></span> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.toArray\">#[</a><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.toArray\">]</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A lightweight structural definitional equality for the symbolic simulation framework.\nUnlike the full `isDefEq`, it avoids expensive operations while still supporting Miller pattern unification.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.isDefEqS","kind":"def","line":1003,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.isDefEqS","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L1003-L1010"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.mkEqPatternFromDecl\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkEqPatternFromDecl</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">declName</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">MetaM</a> (<a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern\">Pattern</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Creates a `Pattern` from an equational theorem, using the left-hand side of the equation.\nIt also returns the right-hand side of the equation\n\nLike `mkPatternFromDecl`, this strips all leading universal quantifiers, recording variable\ntypes and instance status. However, instead of using the entire resulting type as the pattern,\nit extracts just the LHS of the equation.\n\nFor a theorem `∀ x₁ ... xₙ, lhs = rhs`, returns a pattern matching `lhs` with `n` pattern variables.\nThrows an error if the theorem's conclusion is not an equality.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.mkEqPatternFromDecl","kind":"def","line":257,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.mkEqPatternFromDecl","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L257-L271"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromExprWithKey\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkPatternFromExprWithKey</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">levelParams</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.nil\">[</a><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.nil\">]</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">selectKey</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">MetaM</a> (<a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">zetaReduceLHSOnly</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool.false\">false</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">MetaM</a> (<a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern\">Pattern</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Like `mkPatternFromDeclWithKey`, but for a complex proof expression instead of the declaration of a\ntheorem.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromExprWithKey","kind":"def","line":248,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromExprWithKey","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L248-L255"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromDeclWithKey\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkPatternFromDeclWithKey</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">declName</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">selectKey</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">MetaM</a> (<a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">zetaReduceLHSOnly</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool.false\">false</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">MetaM</a> (<a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern\">Pattern</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Creates a `Pattern` from a theorem, using the supplied selection function to extract the key from\nthe theorem's result type.\n\nThis function is used to implement `mkEqPatternFromDecl`.\nLike `mkPatternFromDecl`, this strips all leading universal quantifiers, recording variable\ntypes and instance status. However, instead of using the entire resulting type as the pattern,\nit uses the selection function to extract the key.\n\nFor a theorem `∀ x₁ ... xₙ, type`, returns a pattern matching the first component of `selectKey type`\nwith `n` pattern variables.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromDeclWithKey","kind":"def","line":231,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromDeclWithKey","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L231-L246"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromExpr\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkPatternFromExpr</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">levelParams</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.nil\">[</a><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.nil\">]</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">num?</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></span> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option.none\">none</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">MetaM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern\">Pattern</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromExpr","kind":"def","line":216,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromExpr","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L216-L218"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromDecl\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkPatternFromDecl</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">declName</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">num?</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></span> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option.none\">none</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">MetaM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern\">Pattern</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Creates a `Pattern` from the type of a theorem.\n\nThe pattern is constructed by stripping leading universal quantifiers from the theorem's type.\nEach quantified variable becomes a pattern variable, with its type recorded in `varTypes` and\nwhether it is a type class instance recorded in `isInstance`. The remaining type after\nstripping quantifiers becomes the `pattern` expression.\n\nUniverse level parameters are replaced with fresh unification variables (prefixed with `_uvar`).\n\nIf `num?` is `some n`, at most `n` leading quantifiers are stripped.\nIf `num?` is `none`, all leading quantifiers are stripped.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromDecl","kind":"def","line":199,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.mkPatternFromDecl","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L199-L214"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.instInhabitedPattern\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">instInhabitedPattern</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inhabited\">Inhabited</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern\">Pattern</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.instInhabitedPattern","kind":"instance","line":87,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.instInhabitedPattern","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.lean#L87-L87"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern.checkTypeMask?\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">Pattern</span>.<span class=\"name\">checkTypeMask?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Pattern.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Pattern\">Pattern</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `checkTypeMask? = some mask`, then we must check the type of pattern variable `i`\nif `mask[i]` is true.\nMoreover `mask.size == varTypes.size`.\nSee `mkCheckTypeMask`\n","docLink":"./Lean/Met